00:00:36.099 --> 00:00:38.599
looking at this particular name of God,

00:00:38.599 --> 00:00:42.939
because there is so much that is communicated to us

00:00:42.939 --> 00:00:44.799
with regard to the subject matter, the name Jehovah Ra.

00:00:44.799 --> 00:00:46.139
And so last, not last week,

00:00:46.139 --> 00:00:50.779
because we had Brother Baloo with us,

00:00:50.779 --> 00:00:54.880
but two weeks ago, we considered the provision of my shepherd.

00:00:55.740 --> 00:00:59.479
We looked at Jehovah Ra previously, Jehovah Jireh,

00:00:59.479 --> 00:01:02.580
my God will provide, and we looked at that, another name

00:01:02.580 --> 00:01:05.279
for God, but Jehovah Ra, or another name of God,

00:01:05.279 --> 00:01:08.419
Jehovah Ra, the Lord, my shepherd.

00:01:08.419 --> 00:01:11.559
But as we understand what is communicated to us

00:01:11.559 --> 00:01:15.019
through these names of God, this teaching

00:01:15.019 --> 00:01:18.260
and this truth with regard to the Lord, my shepherd,

00:01:18.260 --> 00:01:21.139
that my shepherd not only provides for me,

00:01:21.139 --> 00:01:24.699
but tonight as we look at verse four in Psalm 23,

00:01:25.519 --> 00:01:28.360
we're reminded of the provision of my shepherd.

00:01:28.360 --> 00:01:30.800
And what a blessing to be reminded of this truth.

00:01:30.800 --> 00:01:32.800
Notice with me, we'll begin reading in verse one,

00:01:32.800 --> 00:01:35.800
we're familiar with it, but Psalm 23, in verse number one,

00:01:35.800 --> 00:01:40.279
the Bible says, the Lord is my shepherd, I shall not want.

00:01:40.279 --> 00:01:42.279
He maketh me to lie down in green pastures,

00:01:42.279 --> 00:01:45.879
he leadeth me beside the still waters, he restoreth my soul,

00:01:45.879 --> 00:01:48.279
he leadeth me in the paths of righteousness

00:01:48.279 --> 00:01:49.919
for his namesake.

00:01:49.919 --> 00:01:52.260
And so last week, we looked at those first three verses

00:01:52.319 --> 00:01:53.819
and we dealt with the provision of the shepherd,

00:01:53.819 --> 00:01:56.680
of my shepherd, and we dealt with the nourishment,

00:01:56.680 --> 00:01:59.279
the restoration, refreshment, the direction

00:01:59.279 --> 00:02:00.519
that he provides.

00:02:00.519 --> 00:02:03.519
And now as we look at verse number four,

00:02:03.519 --> 00:02:05.680
really we're reminded of what we'll look at tonight

00:02:05.680 --> 00:02:08.399
and then also next week, it kind of segues into it.

00:02:08.399 --> 00:02:10.000
But we see in verse number four, the Bible says,

00:02:10.000 --> 00:02:12.240
yea, though I walk through the valley

00:02:12.240 --> 00:02:15.600
of the shadow of death, I will fear no evil,

00:02:15.600 --> 00:02:19.039
for thou art with me, thy rod and thy staff,

00:02:19.039 --> 00:02:20.600
they comfort me.

00:02:20.619 --> 00:02:22.059
Begin to look at verse number four

00:02:22.059 --> 00:02:23.779
and we find not only the protection,

00:02:23.779 --> 00:02:25.619
but also the presence of our shepherd

00:02:25.619 --> 00:02:27.419
and we'll deal with the protection this week

00:02:27.419 --> 00:02:30.380
and next week, we'll look at the presence of our shepherd

00:02:30.380 --> 00:02:32.179
and what a blessing it is to know

00:02:32.179 --> 00:02:34.039
that he'll never leave us nor forsake us.

00:02:34.039 --> 00:02:38.279
But tonight as we focus on the protection of my shepherd,

00:02:38.279 --> 00:02:41.779
I'm reminded that David as a shepherd himself,

00:02:41.779 --> 00:02:44.740
remember, we dealt with several weeks ago,

00:02:44.740 --> 00:02:47.899
the instrument, the human instrument that God used

00:02:47.919 --> 00:02:50.919
to reveal to us this name, Jehovah-Raw,

00:02:50.919 --> 00:02:53.600
was David who himself was a shepherd.

00:02:53.600 --> 00:02:57.000
And so therefore, immediately David would be able

00:02:57.000 --> 00:03:01.000
to relate with various aspects of what's being communicated

00:03:01.000 --> 00:03:04.199
through this name Jehovah-Raw, the Lord my shepherd.

00:03:04.199 --> 00:03:05.639
And so as we look at verse number four

00:03:05.639 --> 00:03:08.679
and begin to think about the protection of our shepherd,

00:03:08.679 --> 00:03:10.919
we're reminded that David understood

00:03:10.919 --> 00:03:14.240
that he was responsible for protecting the flock.

00:03:14.240 --> 00:03:16.820
David understood that he had been entrusted

00:03:16.839 --> 00:03:19.520
with the responsibility of that flock

00:03:19.520 --> 00:03:21.720
and the sheep that his family had.

00:03:21.720 --> 00:03:23.559
And as he was in that position,

00:03:23.559 --> 00:03:25.639
he understood that there were several things

00:03:25.639 --> 00:03:30.199
that he was required to do or responsible for doing,

00:03:30.199 --> 00:03:32.360
those duties that he would fulfill.

00:03:32.360 --> 00:03:34.820
And one of them was in providing protection.

00:03:34.820 --> 00:03:38.839
In fact, we know that when David is having a conversation

00:03:38.839 --> 00:03:41.960
with King Saul, he mentions to King Saul

00:03:41.960 --> 00:03:44.320
about an occasion that he had

00:03:44.320 --> 00:03:46.559
in which he had to protect the sheep.

00:03:47.300 --> 00:03:48.500
And we look at that text of scripture,

00:03:48.500 --> 00:03:51.000
we'll look there quickly, 1 Samuel 17,

00:03:51.000 --> 00:03:52.779
but as we look at that text of scripture,

00:03:52.779 --> 00:03:55.419
I doubt that it was the only time

00:03:55.419 --> 00:03:59.679
that David had a situation in which he had to step in

00:03:59.679 --> 00:04:03.500
and provide some level of protection for the sheep.

00:04:03.500 --> 00:04:05.919
Why? Because sheep need protection.

00:04:06.779 --> 00:04:11.460
There's many dangers, there's many dangers that they face.

00:04:11.460 --> 00:04:14.160
And so we find that here, David,

00:04:14.160 --> 00:04:16.100
as he's speaking with King Saul,

00:04:16.940 --> 00:04:20.100
he says to him in verse 34, 1 Samuel 17,

00:04:20.100 --> 00:04:21.619
and David said unto Saul,

00:04:21.619 --> 00:04:24.459
thy servant kept his father's sheep.

00:04:24.459 --> 00:04:26.079
And there came a lion and a bear

00:04:26.079 --> 00:04:27.700
and took a lamb out of the flock.

00:04:27.700 --> 00:04:30.420
And I went out after him and smote him

00:04:30.420 --> 00:04:32.019
and delivered it out of his mouth.

00:04:32.019 --> 00:04:33.299
And when he arose against me,

00:04:33.299 --> 00:04:37.019
I caught him by his beard and smote him and slew him.

00:04:37.019 --> 00:04:39.420
He acknowledges later in the passage of scripture

00:04:39.420 --> 00:04:42.100
that it was God who gave him the victory.

00:04:42.100 --> 00:04:44.739
He also acknowledges that the same God

00:04:44.739 --> 00:04:48.299
that was enabling him to kill the bear and the lion,

00:04:48.299 --> 00:04:51.660
that that same God would give him victory over Goliath.

00:04:51.660 --> 00:04:53.880
And we understand the greater context there,

00:04:53.880 --> 00:04:55.579
but this evening, as we're considering

00:04:55.579 --> 00:04:58.059
the protection of my shepherd, Jehovah-Rah,

00:04:58.059 --> 00:05:01.380
the Lord, my shepherd, and how he protects us,

00:05:01.380 --> 00:05:04.440
we're reminded that sheep need protection.

00:05:05.480 --> 00:05:07.140
There are many dangers.

00:05:07.140 --> 00:05:09.059
And so David would understand that.

00:05:09.059 --> 00:05:12.100
David knew personally what it was

00:05:12.100 --> 00:05:16.940
to provide a safety, a measure of safety for the sheep.

00:05:16.940 --> 00:05:18.940
And just as sheep face danger,

00:05:18.940 --> 00:05:21.500
it's important that we understand this evening

00:05:21.500 --> 00:05:24.179
that we face great danger as well.

00:05:24.179 --> 00:05:25.700
We have an enemy.

00:05:25.700 --> 00:05:27.279
We have an enemy.

00:05:27.279 --> 00:05:30.820
We find this evening that as we begin to understand

00:05:30.820 --> 00:05:32.859
the truth that the Lord is my shepherd,

00:05:32.859 --> 00:05:35.019
Jehovah-Rah, and he protects me,

00:05:35.019 --> 00:05:38.100
I'm reminded Psalm 121, turn there if you will.

00:05:38.100 --> 00:05:41.980
In Psalm 121, we begin to look at this familiar Psalm

00:05:42.859 --> 00:05:44.820
and we find that there's a reference

00:05:44.820 --> 00:05:47.260
and we actually made up a song

00:05:47.260 --> 00:05:49.899
from verses one and two several years ago.

00:05:49.899 --> 00:05:52.019
I think it was in 2020, actually,

00:05:52.019 --> 00:05:55.540
when we dealt with this particular thought

00:05:55.540 --> 00:05:57.100
of looking unto Jesus.

00:05:57.100 --> 00:05:59.700
And the Psalm begins in verse number one,

00:05:59.700 --> 00:06:02.019
I will lift up mine eyes unto the hills

00:06:02.019 --> 00:06:03.660
from whence cometh my help.

00:06:03.660 --> 00:06:06.059
My help cometh from the Lord, which made heaven and earth.

00:06:06.059 --> 00:06:09.739
And we rejoice in the promises and the principles

00:06:09.739 --> 00:06:11.380
here in verses one and two.

00:06:11.380 --> 00:06:13.940
But then as we continue through the chapter,

00:06:13.940 --> 00:06:17.619
notice in verse number three, the Bible says he,

00:06:17.619 --> 00:06:18.459
who's he?

00:06:18.459 --> 00:06:20.380
Well, that's the Lord, that's my helper.

00:06:20.380 --> 00:06:23.339
It says he, the one who created heaven and earth,

00:06:23.339 --> 00:06:27.380
he will not suffer thy foot to be moved.

00:06:27.380 --> 00:06:31.739
Notice this phrase, he that keepeth thee

00:06:31.739 --> 00:06:35.079
will not slumber.

00:06:36.859 --> 00:06:38.059
You see that?

00:06:38.100 --> 00:06:41.859
He that keepeth thee will not slumber.

00:06:42.779 --> 00:06:44.380
You know, there's never a time

00:06:44.380 --> 00:06:47.619
when our shepherd isn't aware.

00:06:47.619 --> 00:06:52.619
He's awake, he's aware, he's able, amen?

00:06:52.619 --> 00:06:53.859
We see in verse number four,

00:06:53.859 --> 00:06:56.779
behold, he that keepeth Israel

00:06:56.779 --> 00:06:59.380
