00:07:00.440 --> 00:07:03.100
Praise the Lord, praise God.

00:07:03.959 --> 00:07:05.980
We find here this great principle,

00:07:05.980 --> 00:07:07.420
he that keepeth thee.

00:07:07.420 --> 00:07:10.899
Our God is providing protection for us.

00:07:10.899 --> 00:07:12.380
When are we most vulnerable?

00:07:12.380 --> 00:07:15.339
Well, when we're asleep at night, are we not vulnerable?

00:07:15.339 --> 00:07:16.899
You think about some of those dangers

00:07:16.899 --> 00:07:19.179
as you could consider that aspect.

00:07:19.179 --> 00:07:22.339
And we find that he is not he that keepeth us,

00:07:22.339 --> 00:07:23.220
he will not slumber.

00:07:23.220 --> 00:07:24.220
It mentions in verse four

00:07:24.220 --> 00:07:26.059
that he's neither gonna slumber nor sleep.

00:07:26.059 --> 00:07:27.420
I begin to think about our lives

00:07:27.420 --> 00:07:29.739
and the many dangers in which we face in life.

00:07:29.739 --> 00:07:33.820
There are times in which we go in to situations

00:07:33.820 --> 00:07:36.859
