00:07:36.859 --> 00:07:38.899
We have these dangers, we have an enemy.

00:07:39.820 --> 00:07:43.619
The Bible tells us that our enemy is like a lion.

00:07:43.619 --> 00:07:44.459
What did David say?

00:07:44.459 --> 00:07:46.220
There was a lion and a bear.

00:07:46.220 --> 00:07:48.220
The Bible tells us that our enemy is like a lion

00:07:48.220 --> 00:07:52.179
and he walketh about seeking whom he may trip up,

00:07:53.820 --> 00:07:58.019
whom he may devour, whom he may devour.

00:07:58.019 --> 00:08:00.859
And we find this evening that as we begin to understand

00:08:00.859 --> 00:08:03.420
and consider the truth that is before us

00:08:04.019 --> 00:08:06.220
that God provides to me protection

00:08:06.220 --> 00:08:08.420
because he is my shepherd,

00:08:08.420 --> 00:08:10.299
I begin to think about a couple of verses

00:08:10.299 --> 00:08:12.140
and we're just gonna use a few of them

00:08:12.140 --> 00:08:14.579
that David uses throughout the Psalms.

00:08:14.579 --> 00:08:17.019
And as he uses these verses of scripture,

00:08:17.019 --> 00:08:19.339
I believe that it reveals to us

00:08:19.339 --> 00:08:21.940
the understanding that David had

00:08:21.940 --> 00:08:23.980
that God is my protector,

00:08:23.980 --> 00:08:27.700
that God my shepherd, that he protects me.

00:08:27.700 --> 00:08:28.899
And we find that he says this.

00:08:28.899 --> 00:08:30.019
Look at Psalm 28.

00:08:30.019 --> 00:08:31.859
You're there in the book of Psalms.

00:08:31.859 --> 00:08:32.739
Look at Psalm 28.

00:08:33.179 --> 00:08:35.859
Notice what God says or what David says here

00:08:35.859 --> 00:08:37.700
about the Lord.

00:08:37.700 --> 00:08:38.900
In Psalm 28,

00:08:42.659 --> 00:08:43.700
in verse six, it says,

00:08:43.700 --> 00:08:45.820
blessed be the Lord,

00:08:45.820 --> 00:08:48.099
because he has heard the voice of my supplications.

00:08:48.099 --> 00:08:50.859
Aren't you thankful that God hears you when you pray?

00:08:50.859 --> 00:08:53.380
What a joy to know the truth of that.

00:08:53.380 --> 00:08:54.900
It says in verse number seven, notice this.

00:08:54.900 --> 00:08:59.900
The Lord is my strength and my shield.

00:09:00.059 --> 00:09:01.219
What does a shield do?

00:09:02.099 --> 00:09:03.619
A shield protects.

00:09:03.619 --> 00:09:04.739
Now, I understand today

00:09:04.739 --> 00:09:07.940
that when we were to go into battle today

00:09:07.940 --> 00:09:10.940
that we may not use the same type of weaponry

00:09:10.940 --> 00:09:13.539
that they use during the time of the writing

00:09:13.539 --> 00:09:14.539
of the book of Psalms.

00:09:14.539 --> 00:09:17.979
And you can look through the centuries of humanity

00:09:17.979 --> 00:09:20.539
and you can see wars and conflicts

00:09:20.539 --> 00:09:23.500
and you can see various aspects of weaponry

00:09:23.500 --> 00:09:24.460
and what they would use,

00:09:24.460 --> 00:09:26.820
but they would understand right here

00:09:26.820 --> 00:09:28.659
in the context of what we're dealing with

00:09:28.659 --> 00:09:29.659
in the time period,

00:09:29.659 --> 00:09:32.900
they would understand the importance of a shield.

00:09:34.299 --> 00:09:35.780
Amen?

00:09:35.780 --> 00:09:38.340
And we find that as we look at the truth

00:09:38.340 --> 00:09:41.900
of the armor of God in Ephesians chapter number six,

00:09:41.900 --> 00:09:44.140
we're told to take the shield of faith

00:09:44.140 --> 00:09:45.739
and we're told that it will quench

00:09:45.739 --> 00:09:47.659
all the fiery darts of the enemy.

00:09:47.659 --> 00:09:49.380
And we're reminded of that.

00:09:49.380 --> 00:09:50.739
But here, David says,

00:09:50.739 --> 00:09:53.380
the Lord is my strength and my shield.

00:09:53.380 --> 00:09:58.380
Notice my heart trusted in him and I am helped.

00:09:58.380 --> 00:09:59.940
Therefore, my heart.

00:09:59.940 --> 00:10:04.780
greatly rejoiceth, and with my song will I praise him."

00:10:04.780 --> 00:10:07.280
David said, God is my shield.

00:10:07.280 --> 00:10:11.780
See, no soldier would enter into battle

00:10:11.780 --> 00:10:16.340
in this era of human history without having their shield.

00:10:16.340 --> 00:10:18.120
It was absolutely essential.

00:10:18.980 --> 00:10:23.060
We find that David says, understanding the truth,

00:10:23.060 --> 00:10:25.700
Jehovah-Rah, the Lord is my shepherd.

00:10:25.700 --> 00:10:27.300
My shepherd protects me.

00:10:27.300 --> 00:10:29.380
He says, he's my shield.

00:10:29.380 --> 00:10:30.900
He's my shield.

00:10:30.900 --> 00:10:34.340
We find that in Psalm 31, maybe on the same page for you,

00:10:34.340 --> 00:10:35.520
but beginning in verse number one,

00:10:35.520 --> 00:10:38.420
the Bible says, in thee, O Lord, do I put my trust.

00:10:38.420 --> 00:10:40.700
Let me never be ashamed.

00:10:40.700 --> 00:10:42.380
Deliver me in thy righteousness.

00:10:42.380 --> 00:10:44.040
Bow down thine ear to me.

00:10:44.040 --> 00:10:45.580
Deliver me speedily.

00:10:45.580 --> 00:10:49.620
Be thou my strong rock for an house of defense to save me.

00:10:49.620 --> 00:10:54.060
Notice this, for thou art my rock and my fortress.

00:10:54.060 --> 00:10:57.420
Therefore, for thy name's sake, lead me and guide me.

00:10:57.420 --> 00:10:58.500
I see in verse number three,

00:10:58.500 --> 00:11:01.020
where he talks about God being his rock and his fortress,

00:11:01.020 --> 00:11:04.279
and I begin to think about the safety or the security

00:11:04.279 --> 00:11:07.740
that is communicated to us throughout this,

00:11:07.740 --> 00:11:10.980
these two references of my rock and my fortress,

00:11:10.980 --> 00:11:13.779
and we see that security and that safety.

00:11:13.779 --> 00:11:14.620
Why?

00:11:14.620 --> 00:11:16.620
Because the Lord gives that protection.

00:11:18.340 --> 00:11:21.459
You know, some of you have had the opportunity to travel

00:11:21.459 --> 00:11:25.700
and to see some of these castles and some of these fortresses

